<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="511" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11–2144: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-21">November 21,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received 9:06 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1881. Announced in press that following new appointments made in party and
                        Government, T. V. Soong and Chou Chung-yueh, State Councillors; Chou
                        Chung-yueh, Vice President of Examination Yuan; Chen Li-fu, Minister of
                        Organization; Wang Shih-chieh, Minister of Information; Liang Han-tsao,
                        Minister of Overseas Affairs; Chang Li-sheng, Minister of Interior; General
                        Chen Cheng, Minister of War; O. K. Yui, Minister of Finance; Chu Chia-hua,
                        Minister of Education.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>